WEBVTT

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:05.919
Hey, Happy Thanksgiving, everybody. Thank you for joining us. Well, praise the Lord.

00:00:05.920 --> 00:00:11.843
I want to give God thanks for all the things that He's done for us. I mean, man, God's been good this year.

00:00:11.844 --> 00:00:18.967
You know, if you go back and reflect on all the things the Lord has done, what has He done for you?

00:00:18.968 --> 00:00:26.214
I want you to—it could be something. I know the Lord's done something for you this year so far.

00:00:26.215 --> 00:00:38.498
We still have 30-some days left until the first of the year, until January of 2025, but look at what He's done in 2024. And what a time in America.

00:00:38.499 --> 00:00:51.829
You know, you can do it wherever you live, just giving God praise and thanksgiving for everything He's done in your life. He has been so merciful in so many areas.

00:00:51.830 --> 00:00:59.562
I look back, I mean, just looking back at all of the things He's done this year, you know, with Megan and how far she's come.

00:00:59.563 --> 00:01:19.575
We've had a great year with her, seeing healings come and manifestations of the glory with the outpouring at the Tent Revival, seeing the Shekinah Glory Cloud, going to see Billy Burke and smelling the fragrance of the Holy Spirit—so many amazing things, just supernatural.

00:01:19.576 --> 00:01:33.015
The words that the Lord has given me protected President Trump from the assassination attempts twice, maybe even three times. Seeing a Red Wave like the Lord gave us.

00:01:33.016 --> 00:01:53.661
There are so many things that you can be thankful for: that we have a new president coming and helping bring a turnaround to America, and just a lot to be thankful for even going into 2025, regardless of all the rumors of wars and all the things that you see on the news.

00:01:53.662 --> 00:02:00.673
Yeah, there's drama, but there's always something to be thankful for. There's always something to give God praise for.

00:02:00.674 --> 00:02:11.113
You know, a lot of what happened with Abraham—one of my favorite verses is that Abraham staggered not at the promise of God through unbelief, but was strong in faith, giving glory to God.

00:02:11.114 --> 00:02:19.570
He gave praise to God even before he saw the full manifestation of what he was believing for.

00:02:19.571 --> 00:02:30.119
Even in the deadness of Sarah's womb, he was thankful, giving glory to God. That was him giving praise, being thankful.

00:02:30.120 --> 00:02:37.039
I give You praise, Lord; I thank You for all that You've done, all that You're going to do, and all You continue to do.

00:02:37.040 --> 00:02:57.658
And so, I just take a time, even right now, to say, 'God, thank You.'Thank You, Father, for all that You provided: for our clothes, our house, the car we drive, the air we breathe, the sun that shines, the trees that are around the earth.

00:02:57.659 --> 00:03:04.995
Father, for all of the grass and for the water and for all the things that He provided. He could have been a really boring God.

00:03:04.996 --> 00:03:14.269
He could have had one kind of tree—it could have been an oak tree or whatever—and that was the only tree He made.

00:03:14.270 --> 00:03:27.479
He could have made one flower, could have made one bird, but He made all kinds of things for us richly to enjoy.

00:03:27.480 --> 00:03:34.518
Isn't that amazing? He made all the different things: all the different kinds of cows, all the different kinds of dogs.

00:03:34.519 --> 00:03:37.452
You may say, 'Well, I don't like that kind of dog,'but He gave you another kind of choice.

00:03:37.453 --> 00:03:43.632
Maybe you like cats; He gave you all kinds of different cats.

00:03:43.633 --> 00:03:49.272
He is so exceedingly abundantly above all that we dare ask or think.

00:03:49.273 --> 00:04:01.086
And there's something—you say, 'I don't have anything to be thankful for.'Oh, I guarantee you, if you just stop and think just a little bit, you can think of something. I have something to be thankful for.

00:04:01.087 --> 00:04:23.321
And it's just like—when you give God praise and you give God worth and you take the time to give Him an offering of thanksgiving in every area of your life, it brings the glory down, because when praises go up, blessings come down.

00:04:23.322 --> 00:04:29.474
He is worthy of it. He is the El Elyon, the Most High. He's the Jehovah Jireh, He's everything that I need.

00:04:29.475 --> 00:04:38.918
He has it, and He's made it for us richly to enjoy. I love that scripture. And so, you know what?

00:04:38.919 --> 00:04:46.638
You may say, 'Well, I'm not all the way where I need to be in overcoming,'but I saw a little bit of change this year.

00:04:46.639 --> 00:04:57.799
I saw a little bit. I may not have my full manifestation of what I've been believing for, but I saw some change.

00:04:57.800 --> 00:05:03.642
Noah released the dove, and it came back with just a little olive branch.

00:05:03.642 --> 00:05:12.150
But Noah knew that was a sign that the flood was over, and he gave God praise for it.

00:05:12.151 --> 00:05:21.895
Just that little olive leaf, that little twig in its mouth, represented that the flood was over and that God doesn't dangle a carrot.

00:05:21.896 --> 00:05:29.879
Like Billy Burke said to us, God doesn't dangle a carrot and heal partway just to lead you on.

00:05:29.880 --> 00:05:40.448
God's a full manifestation God. So if you've seen something, there's hope in that. There's hope in that little bit of a turnaround.

00:05:40.449 --> 00:05:52.279
That's that olive leaf that you've got today to say, 'God, I have something to be thankful for today,'regardless of how much more you have to go.

00:05:52.280 --> 00:05:58.032
You got the olive leaf; it was the sign that the flood was over.

00:05:58.033 --> 00:06:06.110
In your life, you may have no pain in your elbow, and it may just be a little spot in your elbow that doesn't have pain.

00:06:06.111 --> 00:06:12.224
Give God praise for that no pain in that elbow, or that little toe that doesn't hurt anymore.

00:06:12.225 --> 00:06:22.252
You may go, 'Oh, but everything else hurts so bad,'but give God praise for it because that's the sign that the flood is turning around in your life.

00:06:22.253 --> 00:06:28.353
Believe that today. Reach out today and give God praise for every single thing He's done.

00:06:28.354 --> 00:06:36.329
It may just be, 'My toenail doesn't hurt today, Lord,'but it's a sign that the flood is subsiding in your life.

00:06:36.330 --> 00:06:45.559
That storm that was sent to try to kill, steal, and destroy you and pull you down all the way under—there's a sign of relief today.

00:06:45.560 --> 00:06:55.719
That's what you have to grab onto: those glimmers of hope. My hope is built on nothing less than Jesus'blood and His righteousness.

00:06:55.720 --> 00:07:05.963
I believe with all my heart that today our olive leaf is here, and we give God praise for that olive leaf.

00:07:05.964 --> 00:07:14.043
I tell Diana all the time we see the change and the tide is changing with Megan on a day-to-day basis.

00:07:14.044 --> 00:07:24.839
Regardless of if she may have a bad day the next day, we say, 'Nope, we're still standing on the good day.'We had several good days this year.

00:07:24.840 --> 00:07:30.079
We had some bad days, but we're not focused on the bad days; we're focused on the good days.

00:07:30.080 --> 00:07:34.226
Because you've got to give God praise for every single good day and say, 'You know what?

00:07:34.227 --> 00:07:43.991
We may have had a bad day today, but we're going to have a good day tomorrow.'Regardless of your circumstances, joy comes in the morning.

00:07:43.992 --> 00:07:58.653
That's exactly right. I believe that we can call those things that be not as though they were by speaking to our circumstances to change. You may be all alone in this holiday season.

00:07:58.654 --> 00:08:10.740
You may be sitting there on your couch and you're all by yourself and you're thinking, 'Man, nobody cares about me.'But Diana and I are here and we're here for you.

00:08:10.741 --> 00:08:15.999
We're praying for you. Know that we're lifting you up before the Father.

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:24.112
That hit me—somebody's really struggling. I felt that intercession hit me.

00:08:24.113 --> 00:08:32.119
Somebody's out there believing for someone to be their friend, and I just want to let you all know we're your friend.

00:08:32.120 --> 00:08:39.669
We're in your corner; we're believing with you. We stand with you when you feel, 'I don't have anybody out there that loves me.

00:08:39.670 --> 00:08:46.659
Why am I even on this earth? God doesn't care about me; He's forgotten about me.

00:08:46.660 --> 00:08:58.439
I'm broken. I have no friends, no wife, no husband. All my relatives have passed on. I have no kids. I'm all alone on this holiday season.

00:08:58.440 --> 00:09:09.278
Why am I still here?'But God has a plan for you, and this will be the best year you've ever lived so far. In 2024, we're going to find some friends.

00:09:09.279 --> 00:09:19.766
Say that: 'I'm going to make myself friendly, and I'm going to find some friends.'The year is not over; you don't have to be down and out or sad.

00:09:19.767 --> 00:09:27.677
It's a time to have joy in your heart, a smile on your face, and a song in your heart, because Jesus loves you.

00:09:27.678 --> 00:09:35.579
Just like we say every day: put a smile on your face and a song in your heart; Jesus loves you. You know, that came from my dad.

00:09:35.580 --> 00:09:46.170
My mom had a lot of hard times whenever they were going through a lot of poverty, and my mom would fuss around the house a lot.

00:09:46.171 --> 00:09:55.214
My dad would always tell my mom, 'You need to put a smile on your face and a song in your heart,'because she would be so fussy about it.

00:09:55.215 --> 00:10:05.259
That came right up out of him. As a kid, that's always been in my heart; it's always stirred me.

00:10:05.260 --> 00:10:18.200
But that came out of my dad because we had such a hard time growing up. They struggled a lot, but we made it through.

00:10:18.201 --> 00:10:24.525
I met Diana, and it's been the greatest thing of my life, just going through life with her.

00:10:24.526 --> 00:10:31.326
And yet we've had our challenges, and yet it seemed like I left Mom and Dad's mess and we had our own mess started up.

00:10:31.327 --> 00:10:38.417
But God has been faithful, hasn't He, babe? Yes. And He's brought us through some trying times.

00:10:38.418 --> 00:10:48.413
But it wasn't something that we got overnight. We had to believe and keep on keeping on, regardless of what we saw in the natural.

00:10:48.414 --> 00:10:54.303
It felt like we were never going to get out of it—poverty and lack.

00:10:54.304 --> 00:11:24.862
But with the creative ideas to do eBay and Poshmark and Facebook Marketplace, thinking, 'How are we going to get out of this?'when you're going from paycheck to paycheck and you think, 'I don't have any ideas.'But God, who is rich in mercy, will give you a creative idea to do something different and then give you favor with thrift store owners.

00:11:24.863 --> 00:11:31.651
Who knew? You walk in there and start talking to somebody, and you let that favor of God shine on you.

00:11:31.652 --> 00:11:37.562
You don't go in there and start witnessing and hitting them in the head with the Bible.

00:11:37.563 --> 00:11:41.952
You let your light shine through your eyes. You just go in there—man, God's good.

00:11:41.952 --> 00:11:51.567
You just have that attitude of, 'I know who I am in Christ, and I'm going to display Jesus today.'He blesses the fruit of your hands.

00:11:51.568 --> 00:12:07.153
It's like my boss always used to tell me: 'Preach the gospel always, and sometimes use words.'I thought that always stuck out to me when he said that to me: preach the gospel always, and then sometimes use words.

00:12:07.154 --> 00:12:11.856
Why are you going to preach the gospel if you're not using words? It's in your life.

00:12:11.857 --> 00:12:19.317
It's what you display on a day-to-day basis to everybody around you. Who are you when nobody else is looking?

00:12:19.318 --> 00:12:25.559
Especially the Christian people at church—who are you in the real world?

00:12:25.560 --> 00:12:38.071
Let your light shine. Showing up and showing Jesus, and not just always preaching at people.

00:12:38.072 --> 00:12:46.599
Show the love of God to people. Yeah, even when we're in a restaurant or whatever, I will clean up our messes.

00:12:46.600 --> 00:12:53.479
People notice things like that; it's your light shining. If you see a piece of trash on the floor and you pick it up...

00:12:53.480 --> 00:13:10.359
yeah, taking the buggy, like Joyce Meyer says—taking the buggy to the stall instead of letting it ding somebody else's car when you drive off.

00:13:10.360 --> 00:13:16.134
It's just taking the extra mile of excellence. Showing excellence in everything you do.

00:13:16.135 --> 00:13:28.113
Being like Daniel—Daniel was a man of excellence in everything he did. We need to be like Jesus, too.

00:13:28.114 --> 00:13:43.013
But the Bible talks about how Daniel was a man of excellence, and I just want to show that excellence that Jesus shows up and shows off in my life just by me being me.

00:13:43.014 --> 00:13:48.093
It's like when I go and get our mail at the post office box—I just love on people.

00:13:48.094 --> 00:13:54.958
If I go and get a coffee somewhere, I just love on them. 'Hey, how's your day?'And just talk to them.

00:13:54.959 --> 00:14:11.306
They start to wonder, especially if you have a good attitude and you display joy and love.

00:14:11.307 --> 00:14:19.778
Joy is contagious. People right now are hurting, and they're looking for authentic Christians.

00:14:19.779 --> 00:14:40.383
As we see things in the news and on social media right now that try to tarnish Christianity and ministries, it's time that we show up and show people we have Jesus, regardless of what they hear in the news or what's going to break on CNN or Fox or any of these other places.

00:14:40.384 --> 00:15:09.131
When they say there's a scandal, show Jesus. You have a platform with the person at Walmart, with your local grocery store, and they see you are authentic, not fake. I love that.

00:15:09.132 --> 00:15:29.958
That's the ultimate Christian in my opinion: somebody who's just in the ditches, in the trenches, cleaning the church, helping out in the nursery, being an usher year after year with no recognition.

00:15:29.959 --> 00:15:38.586
If it wasn't for you ushering and being a door greeter, would that person who came that wasn't saved feel welcome?

00:15:38.587 --> 00:16:02.752
It's the small things that make the unbeliever see a relationship with the Lord and find it.

00:16:02.753 --> 00:16:16.234
It's that one word of kindness that changes people. So, be thankful today.

00:16:16.235 --> 00:16:25.158
Be thankful for everything. I pray that this blessed you today. We're going to pray with you now.

00:16:25.159 --> 00:16:42.231
I want you to agree with me that every need you have is met, that we take authority over this war, that there are no major wars coming, that we would have peace, and that God would give us an extended time of Grace.

00:16:42.231 --> 00:16:59.812
That's what He said: pray for this. Pray that President Trump has supernatural wisdom in leading this country, that when he is inaugurated on January 20th, we will have a supernatural turnaround.

00:16:59.813 --> 00:17:11.223
God, who is rich in mercy, shows up and shows off in a major way because His people who are called by His name are praying and turning from their wicked ways.

00:17:11.224 --> 00:17:16.496
Father, we just thank You, Lord, for every single person who's represented here today.

00:17:16.497 --> 00:17:25.722
They may be alone, they may be thinking, 'I don't have anybody,'but God, You're there too.

00:17:25.723 --> 00:17:35.038
As we lift them up to You, we lift up their hearts and that loneliness.

00:17:35.039 --> 00:17:45.742
Holy Spirit, we ask You to go right where they are right now and fill them with Your Shekinah Glory and Your presence.

00:17:45.743 --> 00:17:53.883
In the presence of Jehovah God Almighty, Prince of Peace, troubles vanish, hearts are mended.

00:17:53.884 --> 00:18:01.959
We thank You, Father, that You're mending the hearts and that in that presence, there's peace.

00:18:01.960 --> 00:18:10.778
I pray a supernatural peace over their life today, over their minds today, that they realize that Jesus loves them.

00:18:10.779 --> 00:18:17.678
I pray, Father, for them to find friends at church and people who would care for them.

00:18:17.679 --> 00:18:45.550
I thank You, Father, as they sow love, they will reap it a hundredfold return—a supernatural seed time and harvest concerning the love of God.

00:18:45.551 --> 00:18:54.062
I thank You, Lord, that You're encouraging them today, that they have no yoke and no burden.

00:18:54.063 --> 00:19:03.358
They have joy unspeakable and full of glory. Their minds are renewed to the Word of God, and they realize how much You love them.

00:19:03.359 --> 00:19:20.158
I thank You, Father, for every single person represented here who is believing for an unsaved loved one, for a child that's strayed, whom they haven't heard from during this holiday season.

00:19:20.159 --> 00:19:26.501
Father, I thank You, Lord, that we call those kids home in the name of Jesus.

00:19:26.502 --> 00:19:36.169
Holy Spirit, we ask You to put it on their hearts right now to call their mother or their father or their loved ones and check up with them.

00:19:36.170 --> 00:19:43.479
I thank You, Father, that they would just come home and restore the family.

00:19:43.480 --> 00:19:54.492
Father, I thank You, Lord, this is a time of great restoration—restoration of all things over our families and our unsaved loved ones.

00:19:54.493 --> 00:20:00.353
We call them born again, we call them filled with and controlled by the Holy Spirit.

00:20:00.354 --> 00:20:05.883
Father, we ask that You would open the eyes that Satan has blinded.

00:20:05.884 --> 00:20:24.376
We call their eyes to be enlightened right now in the name of Jesus. I speak to their ears to hear You, Lord, right now.

00:20:24.377 --> 00:20:38.451
All the demonic spirits that have been lying to them and speaking perverse things—we command them to go now in Jesus'name.

00:20:38.452 --> 00:20:44.345
We speak to their ears to pop open; they would hear Your voice, Lord.

00:20:44.346 --> 00:20:52.489
Be saved, be born again, turn from your wicked ways. I thank You, Lord, that they would hear You.

00:20:52.490 --> 00:21:02.599
We call forth the greatest harvest of souls this world has ever known, in the name of Jesus.

00:21:02.600 --> 00:21:11.689
We're calling those souls in. We thank You, Lord, that the laborers are coming, the harvesters are coming.

00:21:11.690 --> 00:21:29.584
I thank You, Lord, that the harvesters are bringing forth the harvest, uninterrupted and unhindered by any satanic or demonic force.

00:21:29.585 --> 00:21:39.736
There is one last call for a mighty move of God, one last call for healing before Your Son's return.

00:21:39.737 --> 00:21:52.379
I thank You, Lord, that You're shaking the churches all around the world, waking up all of the people who are asleep.

00:21:52.380 --> 00:22:07.479
Shaking the churches and the pulpits so that the great move of God would flow like a mighty rushing wind, bringing forth the great harvest and the light of God would shine in the name of Jesus.

00:22:07.480 --> 00:22:16.272
Even among the Latter-day Saints, Father, that they would turn and have a revelation knowledge of who You are at a greater level.

00:22:16.273 --> 00:22:29.460
Father, I thank You, Lord, that we come against false religion and all kinds of demonic spirits.

00:22:29.461 --> 00:22:39.066
We thank You, Lord, for an authentic move of God in the churches.

00:22:39.067 --> 00:22:45.985
Thank You, Father, that You would show us where we are in error in our ways.

00:22:45.986 --> 00:22:55.522
I thank You, Lord, that You're exposing false doctrines and false religion.

00:22:55.523 --> 00:23:07.143
I thank You, Lord, that You expose this, that the eyes of their understanding would be enlightened in the name of Jesus.

00:23:07.144 --> 00:23:24.965
We plead the blood of Jesus Christ over every single person represented here today. Jesus has a plan for every single one of us.

00:23:24.966 --> 00:23:43.900
Let there be a mighty rushing wind of Your Spirit upon this earth one last time, just like it was in Acts chapter 2.

00:23:43.901 --> 00:23:56.143
Father, I thank You, Lord, for a fresh touch, a fresh presence, a fresh anointing on every single person.

00:23:56.144 --> 00:24:27.368
Fan the flame, oh God! Stir in them right now in Jesus'name. Shaking off all the bondage, taking off the scales of religion and perverse, reprobate thinking.

00:24:27.369 --> 00:24:47.080
Bringing them close to the fire and the heart of God. That they repent and turn from their wicked ways, that they humble themselves and pray and seek Your face, Lord.

00:24:47.081 --> 00:24:56.592
This is a time like never before to run back to the altars and repent, to bring the glory back into our churches.

00:24:56.593 --> 00:25:09.469
Shake the religious spirits out of the churches and bring forth fresh fire, a fresh presence on Your churches, Lord.

00:25:09.470 --> 00:25:43.779
Shaking the seeker-friendlies, shaking the lukewarm. We thank You, Father, for Your creative miracles and for healings.

00:25:43.780 --> 00:25:52.763
We call forth explosions of Your glory inside of these churches.

00:25:52.764 --> 00:26:19.006
Father, when the pastor preaches, let the presence of God weigh so strong that there would be a holy hush upon the congregation—a holy glory throughout the congregation.

00:26:19.007 --> 00:26:29.820
As that comes on that congregation, Lord, a great repentance, a great holiness, a great outcry of Your Spirit would stir up inside of them.

